# Antigravity — Documentation Updates

Read `context.md` for project overview. Read `.agents/AGENTS.md` before changing trading/runtime code.

## After every code/config/dashboard/trading change

1. **`.agents/AGENTS.md`** — append Change Log entry (`### YYYY-MM-DD: title`) in the same work session
2. Include: files changed, problem/goal, fix, impact, verify steps
3. If committing, include `AGENTS.md` in the same commit

## Also update `context.md` when the big picture changes

Update in the **same work session** if any of these changed:

- Tab map (add/remove tab, timeframe, evaluator wiring)
- Architecture (new loops, signal flow, core file moves)
- Important defaults in `config.py` (`STARTUP_ENABLED_TABS`, notional, max positions, scan limit)
- New env vars affecting runtime (`LOCAL_SLTP`, `ORDER_ENV` behavior, etc.)
- `paper_state.json` schema or critical invariants (hedge rules, state keys)
- New frequently-used API endpoints or scripts

**Do not** update `context.md` for small bug fixes, minor UI tweaks, or parameter-only strategy tweaks — `AGENTS.md` Change Log is enough.

## Checklist before finishing a task

- [ ] `AGENTS.md` Change Log updated?
- [ ] Big-picture change → `context.md` updated too?
- [ ] Hedge/order/sync edits → ran `tests/test_server_hedge.py`?
